data.title: Actors’ Strike: Hollywood Stars on the Picket Lines
data.meta_description: SAG-AFTRA, the actors’ guild representing 160,000 actors, has joined the WGA on strike. Here are the biggest stars who’ve joined the fight.
data.text:
Jane Fonda

Jane Fonda speaks to the crowd as Starbucks workers stand on the picket line with striking SAG-AFTRA and Writers Guild of America (WGA) members in solidarity outside Netflix studios on July 28, 2023, in Los Angeles, California. The show of support is part of a Starbucks Workers United ‘The Union is Calling’ summer bus tour across 13 cities in an effort to unionize more Starbucks stores with workers calling for a living wage and other protections amid a so-called “hot labor summer.”

Jeremy Allen White

The Bear star Jeremy Allen White walks the picket line and raises a sign in support of the SAG-AFTRA and WGA strike on July 20, 2023, in Los Angeles, California.

Adam Sandler and Ben Stiller

Adam Sandler and Ben Stiller are seen at the SAG-AFTRA strike in Midtown Manhattan on August 2, 2023, in New York City.

Bryan Cranston

Breaking Bad star Bryan Cranston speaks during a SAG-AFTRA “Rock The City For A Fair Contract” strike rally at Times Square on July 25, 2023, in New York City.

Steve Buscemi, Brendan Fraser and Christian Slater

Steve Buscemi, Brendan Fraser, and Christian Slater are seen at the SAG-AFTRA Strike in Times Square on July 25, 2023, in New York City.

Mandy Moore

Actress Mandy Moore joins SAG-AFTRA and WGA members as they walk the picket line at The Walt Disney Co. studios on July 14, 2023, in Burbank, California.

America Ferrera

Barbie star America Ferrera (R) joins SAG-AFTRA members on the picket line in front of Netflix and Warner Bros on July 19, 2023, in New York City.

Anna Kendrick

Actress Anna Kendrick and writer Larry Karaszewski join members and supporters of SAG-AFTRA and WGA on the picket line at Fox Studios on August 1, 2023, in Los Angeles, California.

Brian Cox

Actor Brian Cox addresses members of the entertainment trade union Equity and supporters during a rally in Leicester Square in solidarity with striking U.S. actors in London on July 21, 2023.

Bob Odenkirk

Bob Odenkirk walks the picket line with members of the Writers Guild of America and the Screen Actors Guild outside Paramount Studios in Los Angeles, California, on July 19, 2023.

Kumail Nanjiani

Kumail Nanjiani and his wife, writer Emily V. Gordon (The Big Sick), join members of the Writers Guild of America and the Screen Actors Guild as they walk the picket line outside of Paramount Studios in Los Angeles, California, on July 18, 2023.

Kevin Bacon and Kyra Sedgwick

Husband and wife actors Kevin Bacon and Kyra Sedgwick are part of the picket line outside NBCUniversal at 30 Rockefeller Plaza in New York on Tuesday, July 18, 2023.

Aubrey Plaza

Aubrey Plaza joins the picket line outside of Netflix in West Hollywood during the SAG-AFTRA and WGA strike for better contracts and conditions on July 20, 2023, in West Hollywood, California.

Jill Hennessy and Justin Theroux

Jill Hennessy and Justin Theroux are seen at the SAG-AFTRA picket line in Downtown Manhattan on August 03, 2023, in New York City.

Octavia Spencer

Oscar winner Octavia Spencer joins members of the Writers Guild of America and the Screen Actors Guild as they walk a picket line outside of Walt Disney Studios in Burbank, California, on August 1, 2023.
